+The previous approach was visually rich, but it left too many opportunities for displays/browsers to reveal banding or clipped edges.
+
+### Trade-offs and alternatives
+
+- Trade-off: the background is intentionally simpler and flatter. This is on purpose: correctness and cleanliness over fancy.
+- Alternative considered: keep the gradients and crank up dithering/noise per section. That can work, but it is still vulnerable to clipping and per-section stacking differences. The global single-tone background is the most robust across Chrome + Safari.
